sections.text:
In all varieties, subject to the special provisions for each variety and tolerances allowed , the leaf shall be: 
 whole; 
 sound; produce affected by rotting or deterioration such as to make it unfit for consumption is excluded ; 
 clean; practically free of any visible foreign matter; 
 practically free of pest affecting the general appearance of the produce; 
 free of abnormal external moisture excluding condensation following removal from cold storage ; 
 fresh appearance, with a minimum water content of 60 percent; 
 practically free of damage caused by pests; and 
 free of any foreign smell and/or taste.

